{"page_content": "![](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/_assets/3137b1a864c689786cac76b3def62dd1/Assets/img/default-banner.jpg)\n\n# Heavy Vehicles\n\nThe SAAQ ensures that heavy vehicles used for road transportation of goods and passengers in Québec comply with laws and regulations.\n\n## Heavy vehicles are...\n\n- A road vehicle with a gross vehicle weight rating (GVWR) of 4,500 kg or more\n- A combination of road vehicles with a gross combination weight rating of 4,500 kg or more\n- A tow truck\n- A road vehicle transporting dangerous substances requiring the display of safety marks\n- A bus\n- A minibus\n\nSome heavy vehicles are exempt from several obligations set forth in the _Act respecting owners, operators and drivers of heavy vehicles_. Visit the website of the [Ministère des Transports⁠ ⁠](https://www.transports.gouv.qc.ca/en/Pages/Home.aspx) to find out more.\n\nLast update: August 9, 2024\n\n## Safety first, on the road and online\n\nWe are committed to protecting your personal information and privacy. That's why, when we collect data, we follow a [Policy on Privacy](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/policies/privacy) that is responsible and transparent. By continuing to browse without modifying your preferences, you accept the use of cookies.\n\nEdit settingsAcceptReject\n\nDétection du zoom", "metadata": {"title": "Heavy Vehicles - SAAQ", "description": "The SAAQ ensures that heavy vehicles used for road transportation of goods and passengers in Québec comply with laws and regulations.", "url": "https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/transportation-goods/heavy-vehicles", "language": "en", "keywords": "heavy vehicle, heavy truck, owner, operator, truck, trucking, road transportation, mechanical inspection, mechanical maintenance, load securement, load, size, dimensions, load limits, size limits, dangerous substances, hazardous material, cargo", "robots": null, "og_title": "Heavy Vehicles", "og_description": "The SAAQ ensures that heavy vehicles used for road transportation of good